# ─── OpenSpace (Mox hardened fork) — example environment ─────────────────
#
# This is the canonical example of how to configure the Mox hardened fork
# of OpenSpace for a *fully local, cloud-disabled* install.
#
# Copy to `.env` and edit. Anything commented out is INTENTIONALLY OFF.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Where the local skill DB + embedding cache live.
OPENSPACE_HOME=E:\GenClaw\.openspace-mox

# Where OpenSpace looks for host-provided SKILL.md files (the agent's
# native skill packs).  Point this at Mox/OpenClaw's skills dir if you
# want OpenSpace to know about them.
# OPENSPACE_HOST_SKILL_DIRS=C:\Users\JRMAs\AppData\Roaming\Genspark Claw\users\<uid>\workspace\skills

# Hard guard: refuse public uploads.  The Mox-hardened MCP server reads
# this at upload time and rejects visibility="public".
OPENSPACE_PRIVATE_ONLY=true

# ─── Intentionally NOT set (cloud disabled by construction) ──────────────
#
# OPENSPACE_API_KEY=          ← DO NOT SET.  Without this, the cloud client
#                                refuses to instantiate (CloudError).  No
#                                cloud uploads, no cloud skill imports.
#
# ─── Intentionally NOT set (telemetry deleted at the source) ─────────────
#
# The Mox hardened fork has deleted openspace/utils/telemetry/ entirely
# and removed `posthog`, `scarf`, and `mcp-use` from any transitive dep
# tree.  These vars therefore have no effect, but listing them here so
# future Mox sessions know they were considered:
#
# MCP_USE_ANONYMIZED_TELEMETRY=false   ← would have controlled mcp-use telemetry
# SCARF_NO_ANALYTICS=true              ← would have controlled scarf
# DO_NOT_TRACK=true                    ← industry-wide DNT hint
#
# ─── Optional: LLM provider keys (only if you delegate tasks) ────────────
#
# OpenSpace uses litellm — set ONE of these depending on which LLM you
# want OpenSpace itself to use for skill evolution reasoning.  Note: if
# you're only using OpenSpace as a passive skill registry (not for
# delegated execution), you don't need any of these.
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=
